 But as I look at scripture and at science, it's actually pretty straightforward.

120
00:05:01,480 --> 00:05:03,040
 Right?

121
00:05:03,040 --> 00:05:08,440
 I believe the reason why Lily, one of the main reasons why Lily is so joyful and free

122
00:05:08,440 --> 00:05:17,320
 is because she is well-loved, protected, and championed, but not just by her biological

123
00:05:17,320 --> 00:05:20,200
 family, right, but actually by a whole village of people.

124
00:05:20,200 --> 00:05:22,720
 As you can see here, this is our little village, our community.

125
00:05:22,720 --> 00:05:27,600
 A group of us there actually live in the same building together intentionally on purpose.

126
00:05:27,600 --> 00:05:28,640
 Okay?

127
00:05:28,640 --> 00:05:33,400
 And so it seems like to me that she is just like Jesus when he was baptized.

128
00:05:33,400 --> 00:05:39,240
 If you remember Matthew 3:17, "The heavens opened," and then Jesus heard the Father's

129
00:05:39,240 --> 00:05:41,680
 voice saying, "This is my Son whom I love.

130
00:05:41,680 --> 00:05:43,360
 With Him, I'm well-pleased."

131
00:05:43,360 --> 00:05:50,080
 That somehow Lily, growing up in this type of a community, she is constantly hearing

