00:05:50,080 --> 00:05:55,680
 that voice, but from a chorus of voices, just reminding her, affirming her of her true identity.

133
00:05:55,680 --> 00:06:03,680
 "Lily, you are a beloved daughter of God, and with you, we are all well-pleased."

134
00:06:03,680 --> 00:06:08,560
 Now through my work at Mother's Choice, I have met other kids in Hong Kong who have

135
00:06:08,560 --> 00:06:13,520
 a very different experience than Lily, unfortunately.

136
00:06:13,520 --> 00:06:16,000
 I'll just mention two very, very quickly.

137
00:06:16,000 --> 00:06:23,800
 My wife and I, our family, we helped babysit a little boy, a baby boy who has a single

138
00:06:23,800 --> 00:06:27,920
 mom, and so this is through Safe Families, Mother's Choice.

139
00:06:27,920 --> 00:06:32,920
 And when this baby first came to us, he was not even a year old.

140
00:06:32,920 --> 00:06:38,440
 And one of the things we noticed right away was just how small he was, tiny.

141
00:06:38,440 --> 00:06:44,600
 And we also saw his clothes, it was dirty, stains, and he smelled like smoke.

142
00:06:44,600 --> 00:06:51,240
 And we looked at his skin, he was covered in eczema, I guess wasn't really well-treated,

143
00:06:51,240 --> 00:06:57,600
 and so many of his joints, it was scratched to the point where it was just bleeding.

144
00:06:57,600 --> 00:07:01,200
 And of course, that was just, to us, just heartbreaking.

145
00:07:01,200 --> 00:07:07,200
 And then we just noticed that even the littlest sound or the littlest noise would just really

146
00:07:07,200 --> 00:07:14,360
 scare this little baby, and he would just cry and cry and cry, and just uncontrollably.

147
00:07:14,360 --> 00:07:18,920
 But the thing that was probably most heart-wrenching was we noticed that he was always holding

148
00:07:18,920 --> 00:07:21,920
 his thumb very tightly like this, his left thumb, and he couldn't, and when you try to

149
00:07:21,920 --> 00:07:27,400
 take it out and engage this thumb, it was a loose kind of limp, and it's as if he couldn't

150
00:07:27,400 --> 00:07:28,480
 use it at all.

151
00:07:28,480 --> 00:07:32,400
 And so of course, we told our social worker, she spoke to the therapist, got it checked

152
00:07:32,400 --> 00:07:38,920
 out, and we found out that it's because this little baby was stressed.

153
00:07:38,920 --> 00:07:43,440
 It's because he was stressed, anxious.

154
00:07:43,440 --> 00:07:45,000
 Stress and anxious.

155
00:07:45,000 --> 00:07:46,320
 And it just blew our minds.

156
00:07:46,320 --> 00:07:50,440
 We were thinking, yes, we know a lot of Hong Kong people, young people struggle with depression,

157
00:07:50,440 --> 00:07:58,480
 struggle with mental health issues, but a one-year-old with mental health issues, stressed,

158
00:07:58,480 --> 00:08:02,240
 anxious, that was for us very heartbreaking.

159
00:08:02,240 --> 00:08:06,040
 Another couple that's close friends with ours that was also fostering from Mother's Choice,

160
00:08:06,040 --> 00:08:10,720
 this was a couple years back, told us about their little boy that came in that was about

161
00:08:10,720 --> 00:08:14,760
 a year and a half when he came into their home, and one of the first things they noticed

162
00:08:14,760 --> 00:08:25,280
 was that in between meals, this little boy would be rummaging through the trash can.

163
00:08:25,280 --> 00:08:29,360
 Maybe he was hungry, maybe he was thinking that he had to take care of himself, or he

164
00:08:29,360 --> 00:08:31,160
 was worried maybe about his next meal.

165
00:08:31,160 --> 00:08:32,800
 I don't know.

166
00:08:32,800 --> 00:08:40,480
 They also discovered that he would hide or put away, store away bits of his meal in different

167
00:08:40,480 --> 00:08:45,200
 parts of the home, like he was hoarding his meals.

168
00:08:45,200 --> 00:08:51,520
 Again, some fear deep in his heart, not even two years old yet, worrying about his next

169
00:08:51,520 --> 00:08:52,920
 meal.

170
00:08:52,920 --> 00:08:56,040
 And again, we just thought, that is not right.

171
00:08:56,040 --> 00:08:59,840
 That is not God's design.

172
00:08:59,840 --> 00:09:04,000
 Something is very, very wrong.

173
00:09:04,000 --> 00:09:08,560
 And of course, there are many more vulnerable, abused, and abandoned children in Hong Kong.

174
00:09:08,560 --> 00:09:12,360
 I don't have time to go through all the stats right now, but I'll just highlight in particular

175
00:09:12,360 --> 00:09:18,880
 that there are over 4,000 kids right now stuck in institutional care, and they stay there

176
00:09:18,880 --> 00:09:22,160
 for on average five years or more.

177
00:09:22,160 --> 00:09:23,160
 So think about this.

178
00:09:23,160 --> 00:09:28,520
 The most important years, the most formative years of their lives, between zero and five,

179
00:09:28,520 --> 00:09:34,560
 or those early stages of development, they are stuck in an institution with no access

180
00:09:34,560 --> 00:09:38,000
 to a safe, loving, and permanent family.

181
00:09:38,000 --> 00:09:42,680
 And again, like I said, Scripture and science shows us that that does not set up a child

182
00:09:42,680 --> 00:09:47,320
 to thrive, but only to survive at best.

183
00:09:47,320 --> 00:09:54,320
 Also there are another 600 to 700 kids right now, children, babies, that are...they're

184
00:09:54,320 --> 00:09:58,520
 born, but they're still spending the first year of their lives, the whole year of their

185
00:09:58,520 --> 00:10:03,080
 lives, the first year in the hospital crib, because they have nowhere to go.

186
00:10:03,080 --> 00:10:07,040
 They have no family, a safe place for them to go to.

187
00:10:07,040 --> 00:10:12,720
 And so the whole first year of their lives, they are just growing up inside a hospital

188
00:10:12,720 --> 00:10:13,720
 crib.

189
00:10:13,720 --> 00:10:22,480
 I don't know if you've ever done this, but I've tried to put myself in their shoes just

190
00:10:22,480 --> 00:10:26,680
 to think or try to feel what these children are feeling.

191
00:10:26,680 --> 00:10:32,240
 The two stories I mentioned, these children who are stuck in the institution, how do they

192
00:10:32,240 --> 00:10:33,240
 feel?

193
00:10:33,240 --> 00:10:34,520
 What are they thinking?

194
00:10:34,520 --> 00:10:42,120
 I'm just guessing, but I'm thinking that they're feeling and thinking, "Where is my mom?

195
00:10:42,120 --> 00:10:44,600
 Where is my dad?

196
00:10:44,600 --> 00:10:47,520
 How come no one wants me?

197
00:10:47,520 --> 00:10:51,380
 How come all the other children have families, but I don't have one?

198
00:10:51,380 --> 00:10:52,640
 Is it because I'm not good enough?

199
00:10:52,640 --> 00:10:54,040
 Is it because I'm not smart enough?

200
00:10:54,040 --> 00:10:55,820
 I'm not pretty enough?

201
00:10:55,820 --> 00:10:58,040
 Maybe there's something I can do differently?

202
00:10:58,040 --> 00:10:59,040
 Why?

203
00:10:59,040 --> 00:11:03,920
 Why is it that no one wants me?"

204
00:11:03,920 --> 00:11:09,680
 Eventually, as they hear that script over and over again, I'm sure they begin to internalize

205
00:11:09,680 --> 00:11:11,480
 a horrible lie.

206
00:11:11,480 --> 00:11:14,440
 "I must be a mistake.

207
00:11:14,440 --> 00:11:16,240
 I'm not worthy of love.

208
00:11:16,240 --> 00:11:17,400
 I'm a piece of trash.

209
00:11:17,400 --> 00:11:19,200
 I don't deserve to be loved.

210
00:11:19,200 --> 00:11:22,080
 I don't deserve to live."

211
00:11:22,080 --> 00:11:27,720
 These are horrible lies and attacks from the pit of hell, from the enemy to steal, kill,

212
00:11:27,720 --> 00:11:30,340
 and destroy our families and the next generation.

213
00:11:30,340 --> 00:11:32,040
 This is what the enemy has been doing.

214
00:11:32,040 --> 00:11:33,040
 He's not original.

215
00:11:33,040 --> 00:11:37,240
 He's been doing this from the beginning, since Genesis, trying to destroy, rip apart, tear

216
00:11:37,240 --> 00:11:41,680
 down families and the next generation.

217
00:11:41,680 --> 00:11:43,280
 So how do you feel about this?

218
00:11:43,280 --> 00:11:48,240
 What the enemy has been doing, working overtime to destroy families in Hong Kong, to tear

219
00:11:48,240 --> 00:11:51,640
 down the next generation?

220
00:11:51,640 --> 00:11:52,640
 What if someone...

221
00:11:52,640 --> 00:11:55,640
 Maybe if I brought a little closer to home, what if someone walked into your home this

222
00:11:55,640 --> 00:11:58,980
 afternoon and began to attack your kids?

223
00:11:58,980 --> 00:12:05,760
 Or walked into your Sunday school here at the Vine and began to physically or verbally

224
00:12:05,760 --> 00:12:09,380
 scream abuse at the Vine kids?

225
00:12:09,380 --> 00:12:10,380
 Would you allow it?

226
00:12:10,380 --> 00:12:14,060
 Would you stand by and do nothing?

227
00:12:14,060 --> 00:12:17,240
 What would you do?

228
00:12:17,240 --> 00:12:25,520
 I think more importantly than just what these children feel or what we feel is to ask, "What

229
00:12:25,520 --> 00:12:28,560
 does our Heavenly Father feel about all this?

230
00:12:28,560 --> 00:12:32,120
 How does He feel?"

231
00:12:32,120 --> 00:12:40,840
 The Scriptures tell us that He sees and knows every child because He lovingly formed every

232
00:12:40,840 --> 00:12:47,080
 child, even the ones that are invisible to society, even the ones that are marginalized

233
00:12:47,080 --> 00:12:48,080
 and forgotten.

234
00:12:48,080 --> 00:12:55,480
 He has lovingly formed with His own two hands every child, and He is their true Father.

235
00:12:55,480 --> 00:12:59,560
 And therefore, He knows them by name.

236
00:12:59,560 --> 00:13:06,320
 For many of us, we just see statistics, but He knows them by name because He gave them

237
00:13:06,320 --> 00:13:07,320
 that name.

238
00:13:07,320 --> 00:13:14,200
 He gave them that life, and He has an amazing future for them.

239
00:13:14,200 --> 00:13:19,280
 And so that's why I believe our Father's heart is broken and burning.

240
00:13:19,280 --> 00:13:26,880
 He has a broken heart for these children, and His heart is burning with anger that anyone

241
00:13:26,880 --> 00:13:33,240
 would dare to even touch or mistreat or hurt one of these innocent little ones that are

242
00:13:33,240 --> 00:13:34,860
