00:28:24,560 --> 00:28:26,380
 All right?

479
00:28:26,380 --> 00:28:34,420
 But also, they took him to Sunday school every Sunday at Kowloon Union Church.

480
00:28:34,420 --> 00:28:40,780
 And many seeds of the gospel were sown into this young boy's life.

481
00:28:40,780 --> 00:28:43,860
 So things started to turn around for him.

482
00:28:43,860 --> 00:28:49,840
 Shortly afterwards, he got into LaSalle College, one of the top boys' school in Hong Kong.

483
00:28:49,840 --> 00:28:53,260
 I said one of, just in case there are any DBS boys here.

484
00:28:53,260 --> 00:28:54,700
 Don't want you to leave the room.

485
00:28:54,700 --> 00:28:55,700
 All right?

486
00:28:55,700 --> 00:28:57,780
 So he defended, okay, one of, all right?

487
00:28:57,780 --> 00:29:02,340
 And he graduated as head boy of the school, prefect.

488
00:29:02,340 --> 00:29:03,340
 Okay?

489
00:29:03,340 --> 00:29:04,340
 Pretty amazing.

490
00:29:04,340 --> 00:29:06,220
 Then, he got into Hong Kong U Law School.

491
00:29:06,220 --> 00:29:09,780
 He was part of the first graduating class of Hong Kong U Law School.

492
00:29:09,780 --> 00:29:16,060
 And all his peers ended up being chief justices and starting their own law firms, graduated

493
00:29:16,060 --> 00:29:17,060
 with honors.

494
00:29:17,060 --> 00:29:19,940
 Then he got into Stanford Law School and also graduated with honors.

495
00:29:19,940 --> 00:29:26,140
 And then went on to have an illustrious career as a lawyer, becoming one of the youngest

496
00:29:26,140 --> 00:29:29,620
 partners in some of the most prestigious law firms.

497
00:29:29,620 --> 00:29:37,220
 But more importantly than that, he used his expertise to help many, many churches and

498
00:29:37,220 --> 00:29:40,860
 NGOs and missions agencies.

499
00:29:40,860 --> 00:29:50,500
 He became one of the most kind and upright and generous men in his generation.

500
00:29:50,500 --> 00:29:56,580
 He even retired early and got ordained as a pastor to continue serving the Lord, building

501
00:29:56,580 --> 00:29:58,940
 His kingdom.

502
00:29:58,940 --> 00:30:09,100
 And I know that this man is a good man because this man is my dad.

503
00:30:09,100 --> 00:30:17,740
 That guy, that guy in the back in case you're wondering.

504
00:30:17,740 --> 00:30:21,300
 I mean there's so much more to his story that I can't get in today.

505
00:30:21,300 --> 00:30:23,780
 But I want to highlight.

506
00:30:23,780 --> 00:30:27,300
 He and my mom, they reconciled.

507
00:30:27,300 --> 00:30:35,900
 He reconciled with his dad and led him to the Lord and baptized him before he passed

508
00:30:35,900 --> 00:30:36,900
 away.

509
00:30:36,900 --> 00:30:40,380
 It's so beautiful, so beautiful.

510
00:30:40,380 --> 00:30:44,880
 That alone is a miracle that is worth thanking the Lord for.

511
00:30:44,880 --> 00:30:52,680
 And as I mentioned earlier, my dad, he was such a servant of the kingdom of God.

512
00:30:52,680 --> 00:30:55,180
 He actually helped start Mother's Choice.

513
00:30:55,180 --> 00:30:57,140
 Isn't that crazy?

514
00:30:57,140 --> 00:31:01,180
 He helped with doing the paperwork for the Section 88 and registering the NGO.

515
00:31:01,180 --> 00:31:05,420
 Things really do go, it's a full circle of blessing.

516
00:31:05,420 --> 00:31:10,980
 And on top of that, what was probably most personally for me, the biggest blessing for

517
00:31:10,980 --> 00:31:18,540
 my dad in this story is that he passed on to me and my wife and our family this spiritual

518
00:31:18,540 --> 00:31:26,020
 inheritance, this legacy, this grace for adoption and foster care.

519
00:31:26,020 --> 00:31:30,900
 And so as you can see, my wife and I and our family and our community, we've been fostering

520
00:31:30,900 --> 00:31:37,980
 these two teenage brothers, they're asylum seekers as well as orphans, Fabrice and Samuel.

521
00:31:37,980 --> 00:31:42,460
 I asked their permission, it's okay, they said it's okay to put their picture up.

522
00:31:42,460 --> 00:31:46,560
 And we've been fostering them, they've been living with us for the last year and a half.

523
00:31:46,560 --> 00:31:51,660
 And I just want to say that it's been one of the most challenging...

524
00:31:51,660 --> 00:31:58,180
 That is already putting it lightly.

525
00:31:58,180 --> 00:32:02,940
 I've never felt so disrespected.

526
00:32:02,940 --> 00:32:03,940
 It's just been...

527
00:32:03,940 --> 00:32:05,500
 Yeah, it's been tough.

528
00:32:05,500 --> 00:32:06,500
 It's been very, very tough.

529
00:32:06,500 --> 00:32:12,140
 But at the same time, it's been one of the most formative and fulfilling experiences

530
00:32:12,140 --> 00:32:17,100
 that not just me and my wife, but our whole family and community have experienced.

531
00:32:17,100 --> 00:32:20,460
 We are so grateful that God has brought them to us.

532
00:32:20,460 --> 00:32:25,140
 And we remind them all the time, we tell Fabrice and Samuel all the time, "Thank you.

533
00:32:25,140 --> 00:32:26,140
 Thank you for trusting us.

534
00:32:26,140 --> 00:32:27,820
 Thank you for being here.

535
00:32:27,820 --> 00:32:33,500
 You are a gift from God."

536
00:32:33,500 --> 00:32:41,780
 And so it's really through just this one couple, this one couple who opened their hearts and

537
00:32:41,780 --> 00:32:48,740
 their homes to my dad in his time of crisis, in his time of need, who made room at their

538
00:32:48,740 --> 00:32:54,020
 table for him and treated him like their very own son.

539
00:32:54,020 --> 00:32:56,700
 This is why I can stand before you today.

540
00:32:56,700 --> 00:33:02,860
 This is why I believe that not just my dad's life and his destiny was redeemed, but our

541
00:33:02,860 --> 00:33:08,740
 whole clan, our whole tribe, and all that have been blessed through my father and through

542
00:33:08,740 --> 00:33:19,460
 our family, our church, our ministry, is because one couple, one family, one community said

543
00:33:19,460 --> 00:33:26,340
 yes to God's heart for the fatherless, the orphan, and the widow.

544
00:33:26,340 --> 00:33:34,900
 God truly can redeem not just my dad's broken story, but every broken story into a beautiful

545
00:33:34,900 --> 00:33:37,540
 testimony.

546
00:33:37,540 --> 00:33:42,180
 He's inviting every single one of us to be a part of taking these generational curses.

547
00:33:42,180 --> 00:33:47,140
 You can imagine what would have happened to my dad and then to those after him, taking

548
00:33:47,140 --> 00:33:52,700
 those generational curses and transforming them into generational blessing.

549
00:33:52,700 --> 00:33:55,380
 This is what God invites all of us to be a part of.

550
00:33:55,380 --> 00:34:03,860
 We all get to have a part to play in that.

551
00:34:03,860 --> 00:34:08,380
 So in closing, you might be saying, "Jason, this is all very touching.

552
00:34:08,380 --> 00:34:14,380
 This is all, you know, I want to help, but I just don't know if I'm ready yet to adopt

553
00:34:14,380 --> 00:34:15,380
 or to foster.

554
00:34:15,380 --> 00:34:16,380
 It just seems so overwhelming.

555
00:34:16,380 --> 00:34:18,220
 It's such a huge step."

556
00:34:18,220 --> 00:34:19,220
 And you're right.

557
00:34:19,220 --> 00:34:22,260
 It is huge and overwhelming.

558
00:34:22,260 --> 00:34:23,340
 It is a lot.

559
00:34:23,340 --> 00:34:28,380
 And maybe it's not your portion right now or ever to adopt or foster.

560
00:34:28,380 --> 00:34:29,380
 I don't know.

561
00:34:29,380 --> 00:34:30,940
 That's between you and God.

562
00:34:30,940 --> 00:34:38,960
 But I do know one thing, is that everyone can do something.

563
00:34:38,960 --> 00:34:41,380
 We should not be trying to do everything.

564
00:34:41,380 --> 00:34:44,980
 None of us should be or can do everything.

565
00:34:44,980 --> 00:34:50,100
 But all of us can do something in the care of orphans and widows.

566
00:34:50,100 --> 00:34:51,420
 And this is why I love this verse.

567
00:34:51,420 --> 00:34:56,220
 Oh, by the way, that's a picture of my wife and I a couple of months ago.

568
00:34:56,220 --> 00:34:59,380
 We got to baptize Fabrice.

569
00:34:59,380 --> 00:35:00,860
 Yeah.

570
00:35:00,860 --> 00:35:06,060
 A little blessing, bonus blessing.

571
00:35:06,060 --> 00:35:08,260
 Yeah, that we can all rejoice in.

572
00:35:08,260 --> 00:35:11,820
 But I just want to close with this quote.

573
00:35:11,820 --> 00:35:20,260
 Not all of us can do great things, but all of us can do small things with great love.

574
00:35:20,260 --> 00:35:24,260
 So again, you're not called to do everything.

575
00:35:24,260 --> 00:35:25,260
 You can't.

576
00:35:25,260 --> 00:35:26,260
 None of us can.

577
00:35:26,260 --> 00:35:27,260
 That's not God's design.

578
00:35:27,260 --> 00:35:34,340
 But together as a community, as a village, as God's family, we can all do something.

579
00:35:34,340 --> 00:35:35,740
 And what are those things?

580
00:35:35,740 --> 00:35:38,140
 Here are a few just to get you started.

581
00:35:38,140 --> 00:35:40,980
 One, pray.

582
00:35:40,980 --> 00:35:42,380
 This is not the last resort.

583
00:35:42,380 --> 00:35:45,420
 This is the first, the middle, and the last.

584
00:35:45,420 --> 00:35:46,900
 It is the work.

585
00:35:46,900 --> 00:35:50,820
 It is the work because there's so much spiritual warfare involved.

586
00:35:50,820 --> 00:35:56,540
 And like we love to say, the care for orphans and widows, it's not just hard work.

587
00:35:56,540 --> 00:35:57,940
 It's heart work.

588
00:35:57,940 --> 00:35:59,340
 We need to be in His presence.

589
00:35:59,340 --> 00:36:00,340
 We need prayer.

590
00:36:00,340 --> 00:36:01,340
 There's a lot of spiritual warfare.

591
00:36:01,340 --> 00:36:03,940
 So please begin to pray regularly.

592
00:36:03,940 --> 00:36:09,380
 Secondly, there are many ways you can come alongside adoptive families, foster families,

593
00:36:09,380 --> 00:36:12,980
 families in crisis that are around you in your church community or in your neighborhood

594
00:36:12,980 --> 00:36:16,340
 where you live, work, and play in your schools.

595
00:36:16,340 --> 00:36:18,740
 And there's so many practical ways to help.

596
00:36:18,740 --> 00:36:19,980
 Help with babysitting.

597
00:36:19,980 --> 00:36:25,180
 Help with taking the kid, the baby to see the doctor.

598
00:36:25,180 --> 00:36:26,740
 Help with their Chinese homework.

599
00:36:26,740 --> 00:36:30,340
 All right, these are all things that in our community, many different folks, whether they're

600
00:36:30,340 --> 00:36:35,020
 single, married, retired, studying, everyone's helping and doing their small part.

601
00:36:35,020 --> 00:36:36,020
 And it works.

602
00:36:36,020 --> 00:36:37,020
 Somehow it works.

603
00:36:37,020 --> 00:36:38,020
 It's God's math.

604
00:36:38,020 --> 00:36:39,020
 It's God's economy.

605
00:36:39,020 --> 00:36:40,020
 Okay?

606
00:36:40,020 --> 00:36:41,580
 And then the third thing is learn.

607
00:36:41,580 --> 00:36:44,420
 All right, learn to do good.

608
00:36:44,420 --> 00:36:45,420
 Right?

609
00:36:45,420 --> 00:36:46,420
 1 John 1, 17.

610
00:36:46,420 --> 00:36:47,980
 Learn to do good.

611
00:36:47,980 --> 00:36:48,980
 All right?

612
00:36:48,980 --> 00:36:51,340
 There are many practical ways to get involved.

613
00:36:51,340 --> 00:36:53,980
 And we are actually, I believe, December 4th.

614
00:36:53,980 --> 00:36:58,500
 Thursday, December 4th evening, there will be an info session where you can find out

615
00:36:58,500 --> 00:37:04,540
 more very practically what are some of the services that Mother's Choice offers so that

616
00:37:04,540 --> 00:37:07,660
 you can get practically involved.

617
00:37:07,660 --> 00:37:10,260
 So the bottom line is this.

618
00:37:10,260 --> 00:37:15,540
 We worship and serve a God who sees and loves the vulnerable.

619
00:37:15,540 --> 00:37:21,060
 And He's not afraid to draw near to us in our brokenness.

620
00:37:21,060 --> 00:37:22,060
 He loves us.

621
00:37:22,060 --> 00:37:23,300
 He protects us.

622
00:37:23,300 --> 00:37:27,660
 And then He welcomes us into His family.

623
00:37:27,660 --> 00:37:32,820
 And then He invites us to do the same.

624
00:37:32,820 --> 00:37:38,780
 Could we stand, please, as I close in prayer?

625
00:37:38,780 --> 00:38:00,220
 Yeah, Heavenly Father, thank You that You are our good, good Father.

626
00:38:00,220 --> 00:38:04,900
 But You are not only our Father.

627
00:38:04,900 --> 00:38:07,060
 You are a Father to the fatherless.

628
00:38:07,060 --> 00:38:08,060
 The defender of widows.

629
00:38:08,060 --> 00:38:12,820
 And You put the lonely in families.

630
00:38:12,820 --> 00:38:17,580
 Today God, would You help us not just to be hearers of the Word but doers of the Word.

631
00:38:17,580 --> 00:38:20,460
 But we need Your help, God, because this is too difficult.

632
00:38:20,460 --> 00:38:23,140
 The task is too great.

633
00:38:23,140 --> 00:38:24,140
 It's not enough.

634
00:38:24,140 --> 00:38:29,740
 Our own willpower, our own strength, it's not enough.

635
00:38:29,740 --> 00:38:35,820
 So God, would You first touch our eyes, open our eyes, give us Your eyes to see the vulnerable,

636
00:38:35,820 --> 00:38:40,060
 to see the least of these, the forgotten ones, the orphans, the widows, the refugees.

637
00:38:40,060 --> 00:38:44,180
 Help us to see them and to see their pain.

638
00:38:44,180 --> 00:38:49,140
 Would they no longer be invisible around us, God?

639
00:38:49,140 --> 00:38:53,020
 And secondly, Lord, I pray for our hearts, God.

640
00:38:53,020 --> 00:39:00,220
 Lord, would You awaken our hearts to Your heart, God, that we would hear Your heartbeat

641
00:39:00,220 --> 00:39:06,140
 and feel Your heartbeat for the orphan, the fatherless, for the vulnerable.

642
00:39:06,140 --> 00:39:11,140
 Forgive us, God, when we've allowed our hearts to become too hard or to become too numb.

643
00:39:11,140 --> 00:39:14,740
 Lord, would You give us a new heart today?

644
00:39:14,740 --> 00:39:19,540
 Breathe upon our hearts, God, that our hearts of stone would become hearts of flesh, God,

645
00:39:19,540 --> 00:39:23,840
 that we could feel what You feel and love the way that You love.

646
00:39:23,840 --> 00:39:27,820
 Help us, God.

647
00:39:27,820 --> 00:39:36,580
 And lastly, Lord, we want to offer up the Vine Church, this whole community, this family

648
00:39:36,580 --> 00:39:37,580
 of God.

649
00:39:37,580 --> 00:39:46,380
 Lord, would You commission and empower this church family to rise up as a faith community

650
00:39:46,380 --> 00:39:51,540
 that fathers the fatherless, that defends the widows, that puts the lonely in families

651
00:39:51,540 --> 00:39:59,260
 so that many broken stories would be redeemed into beautiful testimonies.

652
00:39:59,260 --> 00:40:06,060
 All for Your glory, God, and for the sake of this city and the next generation, God.

653
00:40:06,060 --> 00:40:12,380
 Lord, may it be unto us as You say, "Here we are, Lord.

654
00:40:12,380 --> 00:40:13,380
 Use us.

655
00:40:13,380 --> 00:40:14,380
 Send us."

656
00:40:14,380 --> 00:40:19,380
 In Jesus' name we pray.

657
00:40:19,380 --> 00:40:21,380
 Amen.

